Text: This week we started with a team meeting on Monday right before we met with Milair to go over our plans.
Gogo and I had both prepared some paper prototypes to test and show Milair some different designs to see what she would like to use.
We ended up having a debate about which direction we thought we should go in with this project.
Roro was insistent that we could solve the entire project using only Excel but the rest of us weren't too keen on that.
We settled on quickly solving the main issues using Excel but creating a more comprehensive application that would be more user friendly and solve additional problems.

During the meetings we have I always seem to get the feeling that Roro over-complicates the proposed solution, I'm not entirely sure if this will end up being an issue that will need to be addressed though.
After our group meeting with met with Milair to go over our UI prototypes and our plan with Excel then the application.
She seemed really happy with the direction we were moving in for this.
She was able clarify any additional questions we had as well as propose some new features that shouldn't be too hard to implement into the application.
I think she is really looking forward to the results of this project.
Throughout the rest of the week I set up Docker to create a local instance of a MySQL database and to process a script that sets up the tables based off of the ERD and put in some dummy data.
I had some issues in getting this set up initially but Roro had some Docker experience and was able to help me work through those problems to get it running.
I then made a C# application to test that I could actually pull information out of the database which worked fine.

Gogo was interested in how to make that connection through C# so I showed him that part so he will be able to implement it into the application that he and Susu have started to put together based off of the UI prototypes.
C# Application pulling data from MySQL docker container.
Plans for the upcoming week: Continue to expand the ERD to cover more cases.

Attempt to put the database onto AWS or Azure so that the whole team has access to itContinue helping to develop the UI on the application and have it talking to the database to pull out data, possibly inserting data as well.
